creativity. Children are, in fact, a superb demographic from which to recruit if you are a terrorist.Small Arms answers questions about recruitment strategies and tactics, determines what makes a child terrorist and what makes him or her different from an adult one, and charts the ways in which organizations use them. The unconventional focus on child and youth militants allows the authors to, in essence, give us a biography of the child terrorist and the organizations that use them. We are taken inside the mind of the adult and the child to witness that which perhaps most scares us.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aChild suicide bomberszIslamic countries. 0aChild terroristszIslamic countries. 0aChildren and terrorismzIslamic countries. 4aChildhood Studies. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 4aSociology & Social Science. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Terrorism.2bisacsh  achild militant, child soldiers, Islamist terrorists, Pakistan, Palestine.1 aHorgan, John.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065198040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501709425zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501709425423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501709425.jpg  a978-3-11-065198-0  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles